Shola Ameobi is being tracked by West Bromwich Albion, Hull City and Crystal Palace after the 33-year-old was released from a contract with Turkish side Gaziantep.

The three Premier League clubs are all keen to bring in an experienced striker and Ameobi would be available for free.

Alan Pardew signed Yaya Sanogo on loan from Arsenal but knows 6ft 3in Ameobi very well from their days at Newcastle United, while Tony Pulis is desperate to sign a centre-forward to support Saido Berahino.

