Steve Bruce is also on the lookout for options up front and the lack of a fee makes Ameobi, who scored 79 goals in 397 games on Tyneside, a more appetising proposition.

He scored four goals in 11 games for Gaziantep but the club suffered financial difficulties and Ameobi cut his spell short. As he is a free agent he can join a Premier League club after the January window has closed.

